ty.";i:9;s:111:"When the door is in any position other than closed and the garage door opener is activated the door will close.";i:10;s:144:"If the garage door makes contact with an obstruction while closing the door will reverse the opener will beep and the lights will flash 5 times.";i:11;s:121:"Incorrect adjustment of garage door travel limits will interfere with the proper operation of the safety reversal system.";i:12;s:55:"How to Fix a Garage Door That Wont Go All the Way Down.";i:13;s:122:"Garage doors are heavy and to prevent injuries manufacturers of automatic openers include safety sensors to stop the door.";i:14;s:99:"Clearly something is binding catching or blocking the door sections or roller wheels in the tracks.";i:15;s:124:"It could be as simple as one of the track mounting bolts has come loose and is binding with the roller as it tries to go by.";i:16;s:37:"It is also possible that the door is.";i:17;s:174:"If one side of the door is not in line with the other the door wont run smoothly in its tracks and when closed one side of the door wont close completely leaving an open gap.";i:18;s:106:"Side-mounted extension springs are installed above the horizontal roller tracks on both sides of the door.";i:19;s:112:"The extension springs are evenly matched and installed to keep the garage door properly aligned so that it runs.";i:20;s:49:"The door closes flush to the bottom of the floor.";i:21;s:47:"The top however is not flush against the frame.";i:22;s:26:"There is about a 1-12 gap.";i:23;s:120:"I removed the sleds and the garage door opener arm so that I could see if those were inhibiting its closing all the way.";i:24;s:71:"With these removed it will close another 12 or so but there is still a.";i:25;s:23:"Step 1 - Push the Door.";i:26;s:71:"Push the door back to adjust the door and get the center-aligned again.";i:27;s:125:"It is possible that the vertical track down the side has gone out of alignment and shifted due to a slightly loose lag screw.";i:28;s:43:"By pushing the door back into position you.";i:29;s:39:"Hi this is my first post on this forum.";i:30;s:82:"I had my garage door replaced four years ago with a new opener springs and tracks.";i:31;s:51:"It is a wooden sectional door with torsion springs.";i:32;s:43:"Everything appears to be in good condition.";i:33;s:117:"I just noticed that the door doesnt close all the way on one side - there is about a half inch gap only on that side.";i:34;s:93:"A garage door that doesnt shut all the way can be frustrating at best and can even be unsafe.";i:35;s:45:"Learn whats keeping yours from fully closing.";i:36;s:175:"Garage Door Will Not Close All The Way Leaves Gap At Bottom How To Fix A Garage Door That Won T Close All The Way Exl Doors Garage Door Won T Close 3 Things To Check Bob Vila.";i:37;s:108:"One of the most common reasons that the garage door may not close is because the lock-out button is engaged.";i:38;s:86:"This button is to prevent the door from opening or closing using the hand-held remote.";i:39;s:82:"To determine if this is the issue press the garage door button on the garage wall.";i:40;s:50:"MY GARAGE DOOR KEEPS REVERSING AND WILL NOT CLOSE.";i:41;s:256:"Probably the most common phone call we get in the service department is My garage door keeps reversing and I cant get it to close or My remotes wont close the door and I have to hold the wall button until the door is all the way down for it to stay closed.";i:42;s:105:"If the garage door opens correctly but fails to close completely there may be one of three common causes.";i:43;s:42:"The close-limit switch may need adjusting.";i:44;s:131:"Your garage door has set-limit switches that instruct the motor when to stop runningboth when it is opening and when it is closing.";i:45;s:63:"Lately my garage door doesnt want to open or close all the way.";i:46;s:173:"Its not a problem every time and I can get my car in and out most of the time without too much fuss but Im worried that sooner or later its going to stick and stay that way.";i:47;s:221:"Use the control on the wall and hold the button to close the door do not let go until it closes all the way If this closes then its a sensor problem you have to do this with the button on the wall not the remote Customer.";i:48;s:68:"Cleaned the sensors still one yelloworange and one green both solid.";i:49;s:143:"Warped clogged or loose tracks can all be the cause of a stuck garage door and if your garage door partially closes this might be your problem.";i:50;s:144:"If the sensors inside your garage flicker and your door screeches to a halt this means your tracks are warped and will need cleaning to realign.";}}